terms.interesting: It has a long history of cultivation as an ornamental plant, grown across the Mediterranean region, and later France (where it is used in perfumery), the Netherlands (a major centre of cultivation) and elsewhere.
They are commonly planted in butterfly gardens as a nectar source. It is harvested for oil, which is used in perfumery; it is blended with sandalwood oil to produce 'attar genda' perfume.
